# ECS Patterns

## Components

Define in `game/shared/components/init.luau` using `world:component()`:

```luau
local components = {
    Health = world:component() :: types.Id<types.HealthData>,
}
```

Always add the corresponding type to `game/shared/types.luau`.

## Systems

Every system module must return `{ system, phase }`:

```luau
local Planck = require(ReplicatedStorage.Packages.Planck)

return {
    system = function()
        -- query and mutate components here
    end,
    phase = Planck.Phases.Update, -- or Startup, PreUpdate, PostUpdate, Cleanup
}
```

Systems are auto-discovered from folders passed to `startup()`. Place them in `game/shared/systems/`.

## Replication

- ECS replication uses Replecs + ByteNet (see `game/shared/remotes.luau`)
- Client requests snapshot on join, then receives reliable/unreliable updates
- Never replicate directly — go through the replicator API
